result.execSummary:
The defendant Michael A. Delcore was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Michael A. Delcore in court with attorney Jessica L Schuster.  Defendant Michael A. Delcore in custody.  Ralph M Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 10CF146 and 14CF108 @ 9:36 a.m. Agreement stated - State moves to dismiss 10CF146 without prejudice. Court grants. State asks that bond be used to pay costs in 14CF108. 14CF108 - Def will waive prelim hrg, plead to both cts, ct 1 withheld sentence, 2 yrs probation, costs including DNA surcharge, ct 2 90 days jail, costs. Credit for 30 days. Atty Schuster and Def agree. Court reviews prelim rights, finds Def understands and waiver freely made. Probable cause finding. Information filed. Charges and possible penalties reviewed. Plea to ct 1 - guilty. Plea to ct 2 - guilty. Court reviews plea quest. and constitutional rights. Atty Schuster satisfied/factual basis. Court finds Def understands, accepts pleas and finds guilty of ct 1 felony bail jumping and ct 2 resisting or obstructing an officer. Def has nothing to say.  Court accepts agreement. Ct 1 - sentence withheld, 2 yrs probation, costs including DNA surcharge. DNA sample if not already done. Def advised of firearms and voting rights.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Probation may be transferred to State of  Illinois if allowed by DOC.Ct 2 - 90 days jail with credit for 30 days, costs, apply bond from 10CF146, if any balance apply to costs in ct 1. Postconviction rights.
